---
// AI / ML Fundamentals Roadmap
---
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8"/>
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"/>
<title>AI / ML Fundamentals Roadmap</title>
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com"/>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=DM+Serif+Display:ital@0;1&family=Plus+Jakarta+Sans:wght@300;400;500;600&family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@300;400;500&display=swap" rel="stylesheet"/>
<style is:global>
  :root {
    --ink: #0f1117;
    --ink2: #2a2d3a;
    --muted: #6b7080;
    --faint: #9ba0ae;
    --rule: rgba(15,17,23,0.1);
    --rule2: rgba(15,17,23,0.16);
    --bg: #f7f5f0;
    --bg2: #f0ede6;
    --bg3: #e8e4db;
    --white: #ffffff;
    --accent: #0891b2;
    --accent2: #0e7490;
    --accent-bg: #ecfeff;
    --accent-border: #a5f3fc;
    --warn: #d97706;
    --font-display: 'DM Serif Display', Georgia, serif;
    --font-body: 'Plus Jakarta Sans', sans-serif;
    --font-mono: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
  }
  *, *::before, *::after { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }
  html { scroll-behavior: smooth; }

  body {
    background: var(--bg);
    color: var(--ink);
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    overflow-x: hidden;
  }

  /* dot grid bg */
  body::before {
    content: '';
    position: fixed; inset: 0; z-index: 0; pointer-events: none;
    background-image: radial-gradient(circle, rgba(15,17,23,0.12) 1px, transparent 1px);
    background-size: 28px 28px;
    opacity: 0.4;
  }

  ::-webkit-scrollbar { width: 4px; }
  ::-webkit-scrollbar-track { background: var(--bg); }
  ::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb { background: var(--bg3); border-radius: 2px; }

  .site { position: relative; z-index: 1; }
  
  .back-btn {
    display: inline-block;
    margin: 20px 48px 0;
    color: var(--muted);
    text-decoration: none;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 13px;
    transition: color 0.2s;
  }
  .back-btn:hover { color: var(--ink); }

  /* ── HEADER ── */
  header {
    height: 60px;
    display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between;
    padding: 0 48px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule2);
    position: sticky; top: 0; z-index: 100;
    background: rgba(247,245,240,0.92);
    backdrop-filter: blur(12px);
  }
  .logo {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 17px; color: var(--ink);
    display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 10px;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }
  .logo-badge {
    background: var(--ink); color: var(--bg);
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 9px; font-weight: 500;
    padding: 3px 7px; border-radius: 4px;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em; text-transform: uppercase;
  }
  nav { display: flex; gap: 2px; }
  .nav-link {
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 11px; letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    padding: 5px 12px; border-radius: 20px; color: var(--muted);
    text-decoration: none; transition: all 0.18s; cursor: pointer; border: none;
    background: transparent;
  }
  .nav-link:hover { color: var(--ink); background: var(--bg2); }
  .header-right { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 12px; }
  .header-tag {
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 10px; color: var(--faint);
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  }

  /* ── HERO ── */
  .hero {
    padding: 80px 48px 72px;
    display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 380px;
    gap: 80px; align-items: start;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule2);
    position: relative; overflow: hidden;
  }
  .hero-kicker {
    display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 10px;
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 11px;
    color: var(--accent); letter-spacing: 0.08em; text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 22px;
  }
  .hero-kicker span { display: block; width: 32px; height: 1px; background: var(--accent); }
  h1 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(38px, 5.5vw, 68px);
    font-weight: 400; line-height: 1.08;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em; color: var(--ink);
    margin-bottom: 24px;
  }
  h1 em { font-style: italic; color: var(--accent2); }
  .hero-sub {
    font-size: 16px; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.7;
    max-width: 480px; margin-bottom: 40px;
  }
  .cta-row { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 14px; }
  .cta-primary {
    display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 8px;
    padding: 11px 22px; border-radius: 6px;
    background: var(--ink); color: var(--bg);
    font-family: var(--font-body); font-weight: 500; font-size: 14px;
    text-decoration: none; border: none; cursor: pointer; transition: all 0.2s;
  }
  .cta-primary:hover { background: var(--ink2); transform: translateY(-1px); }
  .cta-secondary {
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 12px; color: var(--muted);
    letter-spacing: 0.03em;
  }

  /* hero right — phase list preview */
  .hero-phases { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0; }
  .hp-item {
    display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 14px;
    padding: 12px 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
    cursor: pointer; transition: all 0.16s;
  }
  .hp-item:first-child { border-top: 1px solid var(--rule); }
  .hp-item:hover .hp-name { color: var(--accent); }
  .hp-num {
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 11px; color: var(--faint);
    min-width: 20px; letter-spacing: 0.02em;
  }
  .hp-name {
    flex: 1; font-size: 14px; font-weight: 500; color: var(--ink);
    transition: color 0.16s;
  }
  .hp-dur { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 11px; color: var(--faint); }
  .hp-dot { width: 7px; height: 7px; border-radius: 50%; flex-shrink: 0; }

  /* ── TWO-COLUMN LAYOUT ── */
  .content-wrap {
    display: grid; grid-template-columns: 260px 1fr;
    min-height: 100vh;
  }

  /* ── STICKY SIDEBAR ── */
  .sticky-nav {
    border-right: 1px solid var(--rule2);
    position: sticky; top: 60px; height: calc(100vh - 60px);
    overflow-y: auto; padding: 32px 0;
    background: var(--bg);
  }
  .sticky-nav::-webkit-scrollbar { display: none; }
  .snav-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 10px; letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--faint);
    padding: 0 28px; margin-bottom: 12px;
  }
  .snav-item {
    display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 12px;
    padding: 9px 28px; cursor: pointer; transition: all 0.15s;
    border-left: 2px solid transparent; text-decoration: none;
  }
  .snav-item:hover { background: var(--bg2); }
  .snav-item.active {
    border-left-color: var(--accent); background: var(--accent-bg);
  }
  .snav-dot { width: 6px; height: 6px; border-radius: 50%; flex-shrink: 0; }
  .snav-info { flex: 1; min-width: 0; }
  .snav-name { font-size: 13px; font-weight: 500; color: var(--ink); }
  .snav-dur { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 10px; color: var(--faint); margin-top: 1px; }
  .snav-divider { height: 1px; background: var(--rule); margin: 16px 28px; }

  /* ── MAIN CONTENT ── */
  .main-content { padding: 0; }
  .phase-section { padding: 56px 56px 64px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule2); }
  .phase-section:last-child { border-bottom: none; }

  .ps-header {
    display: flex; align-items: flex-start; justify-content: space-between;
    margin-bottom: 32px; gap: 24px;
  }
  .ps-left {}
  .ps-phase-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 10px; letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--faint); margin-bottom: 8px;
  }
  .ps-title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 32px; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: -0.02em; color: var(--ink);
    display: flex; align-items: baseline; gap: 12px; margin-bottom: 10px;
  }
  .ps-title-color { /* set per phase via inline */ }
  .ps-dur {
    display: inline-block;
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 11px;
    padding: 3px 10px; border-radius: 20px;
    background: var(--bg2); color: var(--muted);
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
  }
  .ps-desc { font-size: 14px; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.7; max-width: 580px; }
  .ps-bar {
    width: 3px; height: 60px; border-radius: 2px; flex-shrink: 0;
    align-self: center;
  }

  /* cards grid */
  .cards-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); gap: 14px; }
  .card {
    background: var(--white); border: 1px solid var(--rule2);
    border-radius: 10px; overflow: hidden;
    transition: box-shadow 0.2s, border-color 0.2s;
  }
  .card:hover { border-color: rgba(15,17,23,0.22); box-shadow: 0 2px 12px rgba(15,17,23,0.06); }
  .card-head {
    padding: 18px 20px 14px; cursor: pointer;
  }
  .card-title-row { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 9px; margin-bottom: 11px; }
  .card-stripe { width: 3px; height: 18px; border-radius: 2px; flex-shrink: 0; }
  .card-title { font-size: 15px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--ink); }
  .card-tags { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 5px; }
  .card-tag {
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 10px; letter-spacing: 0.03em;
    padding: 2px 8px; border-radius: 4px; border: 1px solid;
  }
  .card-expand {
    overflow: hidden; max-height: 0; transition: max-height 0.35s cubic-bezier(.4,0,.2,1);
  }
  .card.open .card-expand { max-height: 500px; }
  .card-body {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule); padding: 16px 20px 18px;
    background: var(--bg);
    display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 16px;
  }
  .cb-section {}
  .cb-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 9px; letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--faint); margin-bottom: 8px;
  }
  .cb-list { list-style: none; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 5px; }
  .cb-list li {
    font-size: 12px; color: var(--ink2);
    display: flex; gap: 7px; line-height: 1.5; align-items: baseline;
  }
  .cb-list li::before { content: '—'; color: var(--faint); font-size: 11px; flex-shrink: 0; }
  .card-footer {
    padding: 10px 20px 14px; background: var(--bg); border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
    display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between;
  }
  .card-toggle {
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 11px; color: var(--faint);
    cursor: pointer; padding: 4px 0;
    display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 6px;
  }
  .card-toggle .arrow { transition: transform 0.25s; display: inline-block; }
  .card.open .card-toggle .arrow { transform: rotate(180deg); }
  .deep-btn {
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 11px;
    padding: 4px 12px; border-radius: 5px;
    border: 1px solid var(--rule2); background: transparent;
    color: var(--muted); cursor: pointer; transition: all 0.15s;
    letter-spacing: 0.03em;
  }
  .deep-btn:hover { background: var(--bg2); color: var(--ink); border-color: var(--rule2); }

  /* ── STATS STRIP ── */
  .stats-strip {
    display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(4,1fr);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule2);
  }
  .stat {
    padding: 28px 40px; border-right: 1px solid var(--rule2);
  }
  .stat:last-child { border-right: none; }
  .stat-n {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 36px; color: var(--ink); letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    line-height: 1; margin-bottom: 4px;
  }
  .stat-l { font-size: 13px; color: var(--muted); }

  /* ── FOOTER ── */
  footer {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule2);
    padding: 36px 48px;
    display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between;
    background: var(--bg);
  }
  .footer-l {
    font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 15px; color: var(--muted);
    font-style: italic;
  }
  .footer-r { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 10px; color: var(--faint); letter-spacing: 0.05em; }

  /* ── ANIMATIONS ── */
  @keyframes fadeIn { from{opacity:0;transform:translateY(14px)} to{opacity:1;transform:translateY(0)} }
  .fade-in { animation: fadeIn 0.55s ease both; }
  .d1{animation-delay:.05s} .d2{animation-delay:.1s} .d3{animation-delay:.15s} .d4{animation-delay:.2s}

  /* ── RESPONSIVE ── */
  @media(max-width:960px){
    .back-btn { margin: 20px 24px 0; }
    .content-wrap{grid-template-columns:1fr}
    .sticky-nav{display:none}
    .hero{grid-template-columns:1fr;gap:40px;padding:56px 24px}
    .hero-phases{display:none}
    .phase-section{padding:40px 24px}
    .cards-grid{grid-template-columns:1fr}
    header{padding:0 24px}
    .stats-strip{grid-template-columns:repeat(2,1fr)}
    footer{padding:28px 24px;flex-direction:column;gap:10px;text-align:center}
  }
  @media(max-width:520px){
    .card-body{grid-template-columns:1fr}
    .stats-strip{grid-template-columns:1fr}
  }
</style>
</head>
<body>
<div class="site">

<a href="/resources" class="back-btn">← Back to Resources</a>

<!-- HEADER -->
<header>
  <div class="logo">
    <span>Neural Path</span>
    <span class="logo-badge">AIML</span>
  </div>
  <nav id="mainNav"></nav>
  <div class="header-right">
    <span class="header-tag">7 phases · ~18 months</span>
  </div>
</header>

<!-- HERO -->
<section class="hero">
  <div>
    <div class="hero-kicker"><span></span>The complete guide</div>
    <h1>Your path into<br/><em>AI & machine<br/>learning</em></h1>
    <p class="hero-sub">A structured, opinionated roadmap from math fundamentals to deploying production-grade models and reading frontier research.</p>
    <div class="cta-row">
      <button class="cta-primary" onclick="document.getElementById('phase-0').scrollIntoView({behavior:'smooth'})">
        Begin roadmap
        <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 14 14" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8"><path d="M2 7h10M8 3l4 4-4 4"/></svg>
      </button>
      <span class="cta-secondary">click any card to expand</span>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="hero-phases" id="heroPhases"></div>
</section>

<!-- STATS STRIP -->
<div class="stats-strip">
  <div class="stat fade-in d1"><div class="stat-n">7</div><div class="stat-l">Learning phases</div></div>
  <div class="stat fade-in d2"><div class="stat-n">~18mo</div><div class="stat-l">Total timeline</div></div>
  <div class="stat fade-in d3"><div class="stat-n">28+</div><div class="stat-l">Core topics</div></div>
  <div class="stat fade-in d4"><div class="stat-n">80+</div><div class="stat-l">Curated resources</div></div>
</div>

<!-- BODY -->
<div class="content-wrap">
  <aside class="sticky-nav">
    <div class="snav-label">Phases</div>
    <div id="sidebarNav"></div>
    <div class="snav-divider"></div>
    <div style="padding:0 28px">
      <div style="font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:10px;color:var(--faint);letter-spacing:.04em;line-height:1.7">
        Math → Algorithms →<br/>Deep learning →<br/>Transformers → MLOps →<br/>Specialise → Research
      </div>
    </div>
  </aside>
  <main class="main-content" id="mainContent"></main>
</div>

<!-- FOOTER -->
<footer>
  <div class="footer-l">Neural Path — AI/ML Fundamentals, 2025</div>
  <div class="footer-r">Python · NumPy · PyTorch · Transformers · MLflow · Docker</div>
</footer>

</div>
<script>
const PHASES = [
  {
    id:0, label:"Prerequisites", color:"#64748b", short:"prereq",
    dur:"1–2 months", phase:"Phase 01",
    desc:"AI/ML runs on math and code. Invest here and everything downstream gets easier — skip it and you'll keep hitting invisible walls.",
    cards:[
      { title:"Python for ML", tags:["NumPy","Pandas","Matplotlib"],
        learn:["Python data structures & list comprehensions","NumPy arrays, broadcasting & vectorisation","Pandas DataFrames, groupby, merge","Matplotlib & Seaborn for visualisation","Jupyter notebooks & virtual environments"],
        res:["Python Data Science Handbook (free)","Kaggle Python micro-course","Real Python tutorials"] },
      { title:"Linear algebra", tags:["Vectors","Matrices","SVD"],
        learn:["Vectors, dot products, projections","Matrix multiplication & inverses","Eigenvalues & eigenvectors","Singular value decomposition (SVD)","Why it matters: PCA, neural net weights"],
        res:["3Blue1Brown — Essence of Linear Algebra","Gilbert Strang MIT OCW (free)","Immersive Math (interactive)"] },
      { title:"Calculus & optimisation", tags:["Derivatives","Chain rule","Gradients"],
        learn:["Derivatives & partial derivatives","Gradient as direction of steepest ascent","Chain rule — the engine of backprop","Gradient descent intuition","Convex vs non-convex loss surfaces"],
        res:["Khan Academy Calculus (free)","3Blue1Brown Calculus series","MIT 18.01 OCW"] },
      { title:"Probability & statistics", tags:["Distributions","Bayes","MLE"],
        learn:["Random variables & probability distributions","Expectation, variance, covariance","Bayes' theorem & conditional probability","Maximum likelihood estimation","Central limit theorem & hypothesis testing"],
        res:["StatQuest with Josh Starmer (YouTube)","Think Stats (free PDF)","Seeing Theory (interactive)"] },
    ]
  },
  {
    id:1, label:"ML core", color:"#7c3aed", short:"ml-core",
    dur:"2–3 months", phase:"Phase 02",
    desc:"The foundational algorithms every ML practitioner must understand deeply — not just as sklearn calls, but as mathematical machines.",
    cards:[
      { title:"Supervised learning", tags:["Regression","Classification","Trees"],
        learn:["Linear & logistic regression from scratch","Bias–variance tradeoff","Decision trees & random forests","Gradient boosting (XGBoost, LightGBM)","Model evaluation: CV, ROC, precision/recall"],
        res:["Hands-On ML with Scikit-Learn (Géron)","fast.ai ML course","Andrew Ng ML Specialisation (Coursera)"] },
      { title:"Unsupervised learning", tags:["Clustering","PCA","Embeddings"],
        learn:["K-means & hierarchical clustering","PCA & dimensionality reduction","t-SNE & UMAP for visualisation","Anomaly detection","Autoencoders introduction"],
        res:["Scikit-learn user guide","StatQuest clustering videos","Pattern Recognition (Bishop) ch.9"] },
      { title:"Model evaluation", tags:["Metrics","Cross-val","Overfitting"],
        learn:["Train/val/test splits done correctly","k-fold & stratified cross-validation","Confusion matrix, F1, AUC-ROC","Calibration & reliability diagrams","Detecting & fixing data leakage"],
        res:["Scikit-learn model selection docs","Towards Data Science blog","ML Engineering (Chip Huyen)"] },
      { title:"Feature engineering", tags:["Encoding","Scaling","Selection"],
        learn:["Handling missing values & outliers","Categorical encoding (OHE, target enc.)","Feature scaling & normalisation","Feature selection: filter, wrapper, embedded","Creating domain-specific features"],
        res:["Feature Engineering for ML (Zheng)","Kaggle Feature Engineering course","Practical ML for Engineers"] },
    ]
  },
  {
    id:2, label:"Deep learning", color:"#0891b2", short:"dl",
    dur:"2–3 months", phase:"Phase 03",
    desc:"Neural networks are the heart of modern AI. Understand them at the gradient level, not just the API level.",
    cards:[
      { title:"Neural network basics", tags:["Backprop","Activations","Layers"],
        learn:["Perceptron to multi-layer network","Forward pass & loss computation","Backpropagation step by step","Activation functions (ReLU, sigmoid, tanh)","Initialisation: Xavier & He methods"],
        res:["Neural Networks & Deep Learning (Nielsen, free)","Andrej Karpathy micrograd tutorial","Deep Learning (Goodfellow, free PDF)"] },
      { title:"Training deep nets", tags:["Optimisers","Regularisation","BatchNorm"],
        learn:["SGD, Adam, AdamW optimisers","Learning rate schedules & warmup","Dropout & weight decay","Batch normalisation & layer norm","Gradient clipping & mixed precision"],
        res:["CS231n Stanford (free)","fast.ai Practical Deep Learning","PyTorch official tutorials"] },
      { title:"CNNs", tags:["Vision","Convolution","Transfer learning"],
        learn:["Convolution, padding, stride","Pooling & receptive field","ResNet, VGG, EfficientNet architectures","Transfer learning & fine-tuning","Object detection: YOLO, Faster R-CNN intro"],
        res:["CS231n CNN notes","Papers With Code — image classification","Torchvision docs"] },
      { title:"RNNs & sequence models", tags:["LSTM","GRU","Attention"],
        learn:["Vanilla RNN & vanishing gradient","LSTM & GRU gates explained","Sequence-to-sequence with attention","Beam search & decoding strategies","When RNNs still beat transformers"],
        res:["Understanding LSTM (Olah blog)","CS224n Stanford (free)","Dive into Deep Learning (d2l.ai)"] },
    ]
  },
  {
    id:3, label:"Transformers & LLMs", color:"#059669", short:"llm",
    dur:"2–3 months", phase:"Phase 04",
    desc:"The architecture that changed everything. From self-attention mechanics to fine-tuning and serving frontier models.",
    cards:[
      { title:"Transformer architecture", tags:["Attention","Q/K/V","Positional enc."],
        learn:["Self-attention: Q, K, V matrices","Multi-head attention intuition","Positional encodings (absolute & RoPE)","Encoder-only vs decoder-only vs seq2seq","Layer norm placement: pre vs post"],
        res:["Attention Is All You Need (paper)","The Illustrated Transformer (Alammar)","Andrej Karpathy nanoGPT from scratch"] },
      { title:"Pre-training & tokenisation", tags:["BPE","Masked LM","Scaling laws"],
        learn:["Byte pair encoding (BPE) & SentencePiece","Masked language modelling (BERT-style)","Causal / autoregressive modelling (GPT)","Scaling laws: compute, data, parameters","Data curation & deduplication"],
        res:["BERT paper","GPT-2 paper","Language Models are Few-Shot Learners (GPT-3)"] },
      { title:"Fine-tuning & RLHF", tags:["LoRA","PEFT","Alignment"],
        learn:["Full fine-tuning vs PEFT","LoRA & QLoRA mechanics","Instruction tuning datasets","RLHF: reward model + PPO loop","DPO as simpler alternative to RLHF"],
        res:["Hugging Face PEFT docs","InstructGPT paper","Axolotl fine-tuning library"] },
      { title:"Inference & serving", tags:["KV cache","Quantisation","vLLM"],
        learn:["KV cache: what it stores and why","Quantisation: INT8, INT4, GPTQ","Continuous batching & PagedAttention","Speculative decoding","OpenAI-compatible serving (vLLM, Ollama)"],
        res:["vLLM paper","GPTQ paper","Hugging Face Text Generation Inference"] },
    ]
  },
  {
    id:4, label:"MLOps", color:"#dc2626", short:"mlops",
    dur:"1–2 months", phase:"Phase 05",
    desc:"Models in notebooks don't count. MLOps is how you ship ML reliably and keep it working after day one.",
    cards:[
      { title:"Experiment tracking", tags:["MLflow","W&B","DVC"],
